<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-225-714  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 225 714.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 1 1989 n313 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novell's next step: vendor homogenizes protocols under ODI. (Opendata-link interface)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shore, Joel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Open Data-Link Interface specification, jointly developed byNovell Inc and Apple Computer provides guidelines for developingthe interface between the interface between local area network(LAN) adaptors and protocols on DOS and OS-2 platforms.andP;  It allowsdifferent LAN protocol stacks to use link-level LAN driversinterchangeably and simultaneously.andP;  Developers have a standard towhich they can design drivers and protocols using one unifiedinterface.andP;  All drivers and protocols will work with each other.andO;Apple and Novell decided to put the specification in the publicdomain and give unlimited royalty-free licenses for its use.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (product development)Apple Computer Inc. (product development).andO;Ticker:    AAPL; NOVL.andO;Topic:     SpecificationsInterfaceLocal Area NetworksOS-2MS-DOSCooperative Agreement.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>